[SN]TITLE[SN]
Birmingham terror suspect 'used paintball to train'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A student accused of wanting to "fight and die" for so-called Islamic State went paintballing to prepare himself for combat, a court was told.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Humza Ali attended a session in Solihull with six others in June 2014 before going to Turkey, jurors heard.
Mr Ali, 20, of Bromford Lane, Birmingham, denies distributing terrorist publications and attempting to travel to Syria for terrorist purposes.
His trial is at Birmingham Crown Court.
